<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading"><a href=3D"http://mainequiltcompany.com/quil=
tcalculator/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener">Click to View Q=
uilt Calculator</a></h2>


<p>The <strong><a href=3D"http://mainequiltcompany.com/quiltcalculator/">On=
line Quilt Calculator</a></strong> is designed to provide you the number of=
 blocks needed to make a quilt based on your input of block size, desired q=
uilt width and desired quilt length. If your quilt will have sashings and/o=
r borders, it includes them in the calculation. You can calculate the overh=
ang of your quilt using the <em>Calculate Overhang</em> calculator. You can=
 also adjust your entries and see new results based on them.&nbsp;Click =E2=
=80=9CC<em>lear Results</em>=E2=80=9D to clear the calculator at any time. =
All fields are cleared when you click =E2=80=9C<em>Clear Results</em>=E2=80=
=9C.</p>
<p>To use the <strong><a href=3D"http://mainequiltcompany.com/quiltcalculat=
or/">Online Quilt Calculator</a></strong>, you must enter at least the firs=
t three items. To calculate cornerstones and sashing pieces, enter all of t=
he items. If you plan on a border or borders, enter the width for each bord=
er. Four borders are allowed with this calculator. To compute:</p>
<ul>
<li>Enter the finished block size</li>
<li>Enter the desired quilt width</li>
<li>Enter the desired quilt length</li>
<li>Enter the finished sashing width (leave blank if none)</li>
<li>If you are using cornerstones, click Yes (requires sashing width to cal=
culate)</li>
<li>Enter the finished width of each border (leave blank if no borders)</li=
>
<li>Scroll down and click =E2=80=9CCalculate=E2=80=9D</li>
</ul>
<p><em>Your Results</em> displays your results highlighted in yellow. Somet=
imes the number of blocks needed across or down comes out as a decimal (sho=
wn in calculated blocks across and calculated blocks down). Since we don=E2=
=80=99t generally use partial blocks in quilt making, the calculator rounds=
 these two answers to the nearest whole number and shows it as suggested bl=
ocks across and suggested blocks down.</p>
<p>Using the suggested blocks across and suggested blocks down, it provides=
 the results for the total number of blocks needed and the actual quilt wid=
th and actual quilt length. If you are using cornerstones, it calculates th=
e number and size of the cornerstones as well as the number and size of sas=
hing pieces required. You can change any part of your original input and cl=
ick calculate to see the new result. The new answer will replace your origi=
nal answer.</p>
<p>In<em> Adjust Your Results,</em>&nbsp;you can enter new numbers for the =
blocks across and blocks down. The calculator uses your original input&nbsp=
;and recalculates to provide adjusted results. These results are displayed =
in light blue. You can compare the <em>Adjusted Results</em> to the <em>Cal=
culated Results</em> to see how the change in the number of blocks affects =
the quilt width, length, and number of cornerstones and sashings, if used.<=
/p>
<p><em>Calculate Overhang</em> will display how much overhang on the sides =
and end of the different mattress sizes. Enter the actual quilt width and l=
ength, select the bed size, and click =E2=80=98yes=E2=80=99 or =E2=80=98no=
=E2=80=99 for pillow cover (tuck). If you click =E2=80=98yes=E2=80=99, ente=
r in inches the allowance you want for the pillow tuck. Then click =E2=80=
=9C<em>Calculate Overhang</em>=E2=80=9C. Your results are shown highlighted=
 in light blue. You can adjust your input of width and length or change the=
 bed selection and click calculate again. Your original answer will be over=
written with the new answer.</p>
<p>Go to the <a href=3D"http://mainequiltcompany.com/quiltcalculator/">Onli=
ne Quilt Calculator</a>.</p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 80%;">Note:&nbsp;This <a href=3D"http://mainequiltco=
mpany.com/quiltcalculator/">Online Quilt Calculator</a> is provided complim=
ents of&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://mainequiltcompany.com/">Maine Quilt Company<=
/a>. It is free for non-commercial use only. Though&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://=
mainequiltcompany.com/">Maine Quilt Company</a>&nbsp;strives to provide qua=
lity and accuracy,&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://mainequiltcompany.com/">Maine Qui=
lt Company</a>&nbsp;makes no warranty or guarantee as to the calculator=E2=
=80=99s performance or accuracy.&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://mainequiltcompany.c=
om/">Maine Quilt Company</a>&nbsp;will not be liable for damages resulting =
from the use of its calculators and the user assumes all risks associated w=
ith the calculator=E2=80=99s performance and accuracy.</p>
<p>The Quilt Calculator is Copyright Julie M. Watkins 2017-2025 =E2=80=93 A=
ll Rights Reserved =E2=80=93 Maine Quilt Company</p>
</article>

